    diagnosis: ["Non-contrast CT scan (gold standard for detecting and locating kidney stones)", "Renal ultrasound (especially for pregnant patients and children)", "Urinalysis to detect blood, crystals, and signs of infection", "Urine culture if infection is suspected", "Stone analysis after the stone is passed or removed to determine composition", "Blood tests including calcium, phosphorus, uric acid, and parathyroid hormone levels", "24-hour urine collection for metabolic evaluation (calcium, oxalate, citrate, sodium)", "Intravenous pyelogram (IVP) in select cases"],
