    diet: ["Limit high-purine foods: red meat, organ meats (liver, kidney), shellfish (anchovies, sardines, mussels)", "Limit alcohol, especially beer (high in purines and causes dehydration)", "Limit fructose-sweetened beverages (soda, fruit juices)", "Eat plenty of low-fat dairy products (may reduce uric acid levels)", "Choose complex carbohydrates over refined sugars", "Eat cherries or cherry extract (may reduce gout flares)", "Stay well hydrated (2-3 liters of water daily)", "Limit refined carbohydrates and processed foods", "Eat vegetables (even those with moderate purine content are not harmful)"],
